Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Custom Group Shirts was established in 2012, however, Jennifer Barker has been designing for more than 10 years and creating team/group competition T-Shirts for the last 13 years. Jennifer decided on the company name “Custom Group Shirts” as it has the option to be CGShirts. CG is an abbreviation that could mean Color Guard. Jennifer started performing with the Lake Mary High School color guard and winter guard for 4 years after finishing her middle school career. After High School she performed with World Champions, Northeast Independent, for 6 years and the Boston Crusaders Drum and Bugle Corps for 3 years. From Greenwood Lakes Middle School to Tarpon Springs Middle & High School, Jennifer has taught several competition teams in the Orlando and Hillsborough/Pinellas County area of Florida. After being a public school teacher for 3 years, Jennifer went back to her true love of nerding out on the computer with her full time job of Media/Marketing Director for a fast paced Cosmetic Surgeon. From web updates, social media content/analysis and print publication creation, Jennifer at Custom Group Shirts has extensive history with Adobe Photoshop as well as creating basic websites for groups/teams. Being on staff and/or the director of teams, Jennifer was always around for the last minute “what do you want to put on our competition shirt this year?” We understand how much your students and parents love representing all the hard work and dedication your children/students have put forth. Being proud to wear and support a group is the same way Jennifer started designing. Jennifer began designing her own group shirts as well as other teams she worked with. Among the FFCC community in Florida, BOA community nationwide and WGI community nationwide, Custom Group Shirts are a big hit. Jennifer always had multiple parents from other teams ask “who printed your show shirts this year?” Even though our printers do an outstanding job, we hope that you can join us in correcting parents and spreading the word that Custom Group Shirts DESIGNED your show T-Shirts!

Description: GPSOX allows solo and small firm attorneys seek and advice from other attorneys in a safe, attorney-only environment.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: GPSOX lets the 560,500 solo and small firm attorneys seek and advice from other attorneys in a safe, attorney-only environment. Attorneys today use list serves for communications for the solo and small firm - the lifeblood of many practices - however, they are 1) bombarded by emails and 2) there is no way for them to parse previously asked questions (or to discuss the validity of these questions) leading to similar questions being asked frequently and also that the person asking the question is hoping that the attorney that can answer their question will read their email out of the (several) hundred an attorney can get on these list serves. GPSOX solves this problem by allowing attorneys to duplicate the list serve through email notifications, but also provides a searchable repository where attorneys can discuss legal issues and questions - to save them time.

Description: Bizzlle has two business models 1) Consumer Model and 2) Business to Business model.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Bizzlle has two business models 1) Consumer Model and 2) Business to Business model. Consumer Model: Bizzlle sells 72-hour online Consumer “Reverse Auctions” where anonymous Automobile Dealers actively bid against one another to sell or lease a vehicle to an anonymous Buyer. Bizzlle's price to conduct such an auction is just $29.95 to the Consumer and is free to Dealer participants; however only the winning Dealer pays a fee. When the Auction Period concludes, the Consumer may request disclosure of one Dealer and Vehicle Identification Number in exchange for placing a flat $300.00 Vehicle Hold Deposit. The winning Dealer holds the chosen vehicle for an additional 2 Business Days, allowing the Buyer time to visit the Dealership and execute a Buyer Purchase (or Lease) Agreement. The winning Dealers credits back the Buyer's entire Vehicle Hold Deposit to him / her at the point of delivery. Bizzlle retains the Consumer's $300.00 as its principal revenue stream, The software for this model is Patent Pending. Business to Business Model: Bizzlle provides Automobile Dealers a Web-based alternative to brick and mortar auctions, as well as, their online auction counterparts. Bizzlle uses the dealers existing, used inventory upload services to provide daily updates from dealer stock to its own server. This allows Bizzlle users to purchase and sell used vehicles to one-another in a matter of just a few clicks of the mouse. It also allows Bizzlle to better match wholesale buyers and sellers to one-another by analyzing dealer stocking weaknesses and providing notification when inventory becomes available within the Bizzlle marketplace.  We provide all inventory hosting, auctions themselves, as well as, analytical services free of charge to dealer enrollees. Instead, Bizzlle charges a small buyer and seller fee.

Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Madronish Therapeutics, LLC (MTL) is a biotechnology company focused on immuno-oncology strategies to either enhance immune response against cancer or suppress immune response underlying autoimmune inflammatory diseases.  MTL is dedicated to the creation of novel, patented biologic therapeutics for their use in the treatment of medically unmet cancer and autoimmune/inflammatory diseases indications.    Biologic therapeutics represent the single most clinically and commercially attractive component in the pharmaceutical industry.  Collectively, current marketed biologic therapeutics represent >$40 billion in sales for their respective sponsors.  MTL technology platform is based on the use of modular single chain antibody format that allows creation of bi-, tri- or multispecific biologic therapeutics.  MTL therapeutic proteins are intended to and will be clearly differentiated from the current standards of care used in the therapy of cancer and autoimmune diseases.  MTL will also focus on the generation of antibody-directed chemotherapy strategy of cancer using antibody drug conjugates.  MTL founder has broad experience and track record of success in both these areas of therapeutic R&D.  Bi- or tri-specific functionality of MTL therapeutic assets will offer therapeutic advantage of two or three premium priced individual therapeutics, combinations of which may be clinically beneficial but pharmacoeconomically unaffordable to both patients and payers.  MTL therapeutics will deliver clinical benefit of two or three such therapeutics for the price of one and hence with affordable price points.  Research activities of Madronish will be conducted in a virtual manner by collaborating with contract research organizations capable of undertaking integrated discovery and early development of biologic therapeutics.  A 3-year blueprint of R&D activities has been created awaiting implementation.  MTL is seeking seed funding for expeditious implementation of its research programs.
Industry Groups: Biotechnology, Health Care, Science and Engineering

Full Description: SpotLoss provides a device that allows you to keep track of everything from your keys to your phone to your kids.  The SpotLoss fob allows you to press a button on the fob to find your phone, or a button on your phone to find your fob.   Additionally, it is a proximity alert system.  You can be notified by the fob or by your cellphone if the two devices become more than 50 meters apart, or conversely come within 50 meters of each other. This would notify you that you left your keys on your desk, that your child ran off in the mall, or that your sister is nearby.  Besides an alarm, you can also be notified to a change in proximity by text or email. The fob runs for roughly a year on a replaceable watch battery without having to remember to recharge it.  It measures 5.6 x 3.0 x 1.5 cm and the carabiner style design allows it to quickly latch onto nearly anything. The fob uses a free cell phone app, and we are planning an SDK for developers that would like to use our hardware.
